title: 820-000165 not turning on
message: Hi guys I have an 00165 that came in with a tiny bit of corrosion on C7615 and R7611, replaced them. Also customer broke the battery connector, so replaced that as well. Now the mac gets an orange line, fan starts to spin, all voltages come up for DRAM and also CPU Vcore 1.2v, 1.3v and 1.8v, then after a few seconds it shuts down. I do get a ALL [U]SYS[/U]PWRGD signal as well at 3.2v. Could this be ROM related, or when the fan starts to spin it means not a ROM issue? I also have clock signal for the cpu present and USB mouse activity, until it shuts down. Any ideas? Board looks very clean.

title: 820-000165 not turning on
message:
Try first starting in SMC bypass.
Next, try known good clean ME BIOS.

title: 820-000165 not turning on
message: Found the issue, some corrosion on U8005 reballed it and working again. Thanks!
